WEBVTT

00:16.800 --> 00:20.691
Captions made possible by
HOME BOX OFFICE

00:20.700 --> 00:25.091
A Division of TIME WARNER
ENTERTAINMENT COMPANY, LP.

01:54.200 --> 01:56.725
( female )
SLEEK, SOPHISTICATED,

01:56.730 --> 01:58.391
SEDUCTIVE.

01:58.400 --> 02:02.552
THE NEW MILLENNIUM EDITION,
CROWN ROYAL FUNERAL COACH.

02:02.560 --> 02:05.927
BECAUSE YOUR LOVED ONE
DESERVES THE VERY BEST

02:05.930 --> 02:09.297
IN STYLE
AND COMFORT.

02:23.600 --> 02:29.391
( singing with radio )
I'LL BE HOME
FOR CHRISTMAS

02:29.400 --> 02:34.520
YOU CAN PLAN ON ME...

02:34.530 --> 02:37.090
( phone )

02:40.530 --> 02:41.997
NATHANIEL FISHER.

02:42.000 --> 02:43.092
( female )
Nathaniel ?

02:43.100 --> 02:44.590
IT'S RUTH.

02:44.600 --> 02:47.421
DID YOU TAKE YOUR BLOOD PRESSURE
MEDICATION TODAY ?

02:47.430 --> 02:48.454
Yes.

02:48.460 --> 02:49.654
DON'T LIE TO ME.

02:49.660 --> 02:50.627
I took it.

02:50.630 --> 02:52.097
What do you want me to do,
o.d. on it ?

02:52.100 --> 02:54.318
OH, AND
I JUST REALIZED

02:54.330 --> 02:56.525
WE DON'T HAVE ANY OF THAT
SOY STUFF NATE DRINKS.

02:56.530 --> 02:58.919
YOU KNOW,
SINCE HE GAVE UP MILK.

02:58.930 --> 03:00.625
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S CALLED.

03:00.630 --> 03:02.689
Why not just cut some milk
with tap water ?

03:02.700 --> 03:04.122
He'll never
know the difference.

03:04.130 --> 03:06.121
LOOK, IF YOU DON'T
WANT TO GO, I'LL GO.

03:06.130 --> 03:08.223
IT'S NOT AS IF I DON'T
HAVE ENOUGH TO DO ALREADY.

03:08.230 --> 03:10.949
I'm kidding,
I'll get some.

03:10.960 --> 03:13.349
BUT IT HAS TO BE AFI'ER
I PICK UP NATE AT THE AIRPORT,

03:13.360 --> 03:15.123
I'M ALREADY
RUNNING LATE.

03:16.230 --> 03:17.549
NATHANIEL...

03:17.560 --> 03:18.993
ARE YOU SMOKING ?

03:19.000 --> 03:19.728
No.

03:19.730 --> 03:21.698
YES, YOU ARE,
I HEARD YOU.

03:21.700 --> 03:23.429
I'm not,
no, I'm not.

03:23.430 --> 03:25.489
LOOK, FORGET YOU'LL
GIVE YOURSELF CANCER

03:25.500 --> 03:27.695
AND DIE A SLOW
AND HORRIBLE DEATH.

03:27.700 --> 03:30.021
_ _You should not be
stinking up that new hearse.

03:30.030 --> 03:32.191
I TOLD YOU NOT TO
LET HIM TAKE IT.

03:32.200 --> 03:33.690
LIKE I COULD'VE
STOPPED HIM.

03:33.700 --> 03:35.554
HE'S EVERY BIT
AS PROUD OF THAT THING

03:35.560 --> 03:37.289
AS YOUR FOOL BROTHER WAS
OF THAT DAMN MOTORCYCLE

03:37.300 --> 03:38.528
HE HAD
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

03:38.530 --> 03:40.293
And who still has
a pin in his foot ?

03:40.300 --> 03:41.528
NATHANIEL,

03:41.530 --> 03:43.794
PEOPLE WANT THINGS TO BE NICE
WHEN THERE'S A FUNERAL.

03:43.800 --> 03:46.257
THEY DON'T WANT THEIR
LOVED ONES RIDING AROUND

03:46.260 --> 03:48.125
in something that
smells like an ashtray.

03:48.130 --> 03:49.722
ALRIGHT, LOOK,

03:49.730 --> 03:52.597
I'M QUI'ITING
RIGHT NOW, I PROMISE.

03:52.600 --> 03:55.421
OKAY ?
I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT.

03:56.500 --> 04:02.951
I'LL BE HOME
FOR CHRISTMAS

04:09.630 --> 04:13.726
IF ONLY

04:13.730 --> 04:19.851
IN MY DREAMS

04:24.300 --> 04:26.757
THAT NEW HEARSE WAS
A TOTAL WASTE OF MONEY.

04:26.760 --> 04:28.591
THERE WAS NOTHING WRONG
WITH THE OLD ONE.

04:28.600 --> 04:32.696
I THINK YOUR FATHER'S HAVING
SOME SORT OF MID-LIFE CRISIS.

04:32.700 --> 04:34.725
IT WOULD'VE MADE
SO MUCH MORE SENSE

04:34.730 --> 04:36.857
TO INVEST IN REPANELING
FOR THE CHAPEL,

04:36.860 --> 04:38.794
OR ADDING COFFEE BARS
TO THE SLUMBER ROOMS.

04:38.800 --> 04:41.928
WELL, I'D MUCH RATHER
HE BUY HIMSELF
A FANCY NEW HEARSE

04:41.930 --> 04:43.852
THAN LEAVE ME
FOR A YOUNGER WOMAN.

04:43.860 --> 04:47.296
OR A WOMAN MY AGE,
FOR THAT MA'I'I'ER.

04:47.300 --> 04:49.723
OR HEAVEN FORBID,
A MAN,

04:49.730 --> 04:52.221
LIKE MY COUSIN
HANNAH'S HUSBAND DID.

04:52.230 --> 04:55.996
GOD SURE HAS DEALT THAT WOMAN
SOME BLOWS IN THIS LIFE.

05:00.830 --> 05:02.650
MOM...

05:02.660 --> 05:05.424
CAN I DO
ANYTHING TO HELP ?

05:05.430 --> 05:07.819
NO, NO, HONEY,
I'M FINE.

05:07.830 --> 05:11.095
BESIDES DON'T YOU HAVE
A VIEWING TONIGHT ?

05:11.100 --> 05:13.489
YOU SHOULD PROBABLY
BE GETTING READY.

05:13.500 --> 05:15.525
RIGHT.

05:26.560 --> 05:29.495
SO, I ENJOYED TALKING TO YOU
ABOUT THAT WHOLE SHIATSU THING,

05:29.500 --> 05:31.491
I HOPE THAT
PANS OUT FOR YOU.

05:31.500 --> 05:33.889
YOU SHOULD LET ME
WORK ON YOU SOMETIME.

05:33.900 --> 05:36.095
HERE'S MY CELL NUMBER,

05:36.100 --> 05:38.489
I'LL BE HERE
UNTIL THE 29th.

05:38.500 --> 05:40.718
HERE YOU GO.

05:45.100 --> 05:46.453
HUH.

05:46.460 --> 05:48.792
MY DAD WAS SUPPOSED
TO MEET ME HERE.

05:48.800 --> 05:50.449
I COULD
GIVE YOU A RIDE.

05:50.460 --> 05:51.927
THAT'S ALRIGHT, I'M SURE
HE'LL BE HERE SOON ENOUGH.

05:51.930 --> 05:54.057
I WASN'T TALKING ABOUT
THAT KIND OF RIDE.

05:59.560 --> 06:01.448
YOU'VE DONE
A NICE JOB.

06:01.460 --> 06:04.657
SHE LOOKS
SO PEACEFUL.

06:04.660 --> 06:06.594
WELL, SHE IS
AT PEACE NOW.

06:06.600 --> 06:09.751
IF THERE'S ANY JUSTICE
IN THE UNIVERSE,

06:09.760 --> 06:12.593
SHE'S SHOVELING
SHIT IN HELL.

06:14.000 --> 06:15.353
( phone )

06:15.360 --> 06:16.918
EXCUSE ME.

06:18.900 --> 06:19.753
DAVID FISHER.

06:19.760 --> 06:21.352
DAVID, IT'S CLAIRE.

06:21.360 --> 06:22.520
IS NATE THERE YET ?

06:22.530 --> 06:23.690
NOPE.

06:23.700 --> 06:25.190
I thought he was
coming in tonight,

06:25.200 --> 06:27.054
SO WE COULD DO THAT WHOLE
FORCED CHRISTMAS EVE
FAMILY THING.

06:27.060 --> 06:28.721
WELL--

06:28.730 --> 06:30.891
BECAUSE THERE ARE SOME
REALLY EXCELLENT PARTIES
I COULD BE GOING TO.

06:30.900 --> 06:32.891
CLAIRE.

06:32.900 --> 06:35.698
THIS IS ONE OF THE FEW TIMES
A YEAR WE'RE ALL TOGETHER.

06:35.700 --> 06:38.498
Alright, don't get all
Pat Robertson on me,
I'll be there.

06:38.500 --> 06:40.388
I HAVE TO
DROP SOME STUFF OFF

06:40.400 --> 06:43.619
AT A FRIEND'S HOUSE
BEFORE I HEAD OVER,
OKAY ? BYE.

06:43.630 --> 06:45.052
FUCKING BOY SCOUT.

06:49.660 --> 06:52.390
( heavy breathing )

06:52.400 --> 06:54.755
THIS IS KINDA
DISGUSTING.

06:54.760 --> 06:56.455
DISGUSTING GOOD
OR DISGUSTING BAD ?

06:56.460 --> 06:58.348
OH, DISGUSTING
VERY GOOD.

06:58.360 --> 06:59.896
I KNOW.

06:59.900 --> 07:02.391
YOU'RE SO
FUCKING HOT.

07:02.400 --> 07:03.719
YOU'RE SO SWEET.

07:03.730 --> 07:05.595
I'M A SWEET GUY.

07:05.600 --> 07:08.091
SHUT UP
AND FUCK ME.

07:13.400 --> 07:15.152
( phone )

07:16.330 --> 07:18.127
HELLO ?

07:18.130 --> 07:20.655
THIS IS RUTH FISHER.

07:20.660 --> 07:23.049
YES, I'M HIS WIFE.

07:23.060 --> 07:26.257
WHAT IS THIS ABOUT ?

07:26.260 --> 07:28.319
WHAT ?!

07:36.930 --> 07:39.057
( screaming )

07:43.100 --> 07:44.658
EXCUSE ME.

07:49.830 --> 07:51.752
MOM, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU-- ?

07:53.360 --> 07:56.295
THERE'S BEEN
AN ACCIDENT.

07:56.300 --> 07:59.394
THE NEW HEARSE
IS TOTALLED.

07:59.400 --> 08:02.722
YOUR FATHER
IS DEAD.

08:02.730 --> 08:07.190
YOUR FATHER IS DEAD
AND MY POT ROAST IS RUINED.

08:07.200 --> 08:09.760
OH, MY GOD.

08:10.560 --> 08:13.791
( female )
YOU CARRY A LOT OF TENSION
AROUND IN YOUR LOWER BACK.

08:13.800 --> 08:17.099
NOT AS MUCH
AS 20 MINUTES AGO.

08:22.630 --> 08:24.359
JUST SO YOU KNOW...

08:25.800 --> 08:27.927
I NEVER DO THIS.

08:27.930 --> 08:30.797
OH YEAH,
ME NEITHER.

08:38.060 --> 08:39.789
SO...

08:39.800 --> 08:42.257
WERE YOU EVER GONNA
TELL ME YOUR NAME ?

08:42.260 --> 08:44.558
PROBABLY NOT.

08:46.200 --> 08:48.225
WHY NOT ?

08:48.230 --> 08:51.154
BECAUSE I'M A REALIST.

08:51.160 --> 08:53.355
( phone )

08:54.960 --> 08:57.224
THAT'S MY FATHER
LOOKING FOR ME.

09:02.800 --> 09:05.394
HEY, DAD.

09:05.400 --> 09:08.927
OH, DAVE,
HEY, MERRY CHRISTMAS.

09:08.930 --> 09:11.922
OF COURSE I'M OKAY.

09:11.930 --> 09:14.057
COULDN'T BE BETTER
IN FACT.

09:20.430 --> 09:22.295
WHAT ?

09:23.760 --> 09:25.523
I'M SO SORRY, NATE.

09:25.530 --> 09:27.691
I HATE TO HAVE TO BE
THE ONE TO TELL YOU.

09:38.900 --> 09:41.994
THIS IS JUST
SPEED, RIGHT ?

09:42.000 --> 09:43.991
PROMISE ME
THIS ISN'T CRACK.

09:44.000 --> 09:45.126
'CAUSE I GOTTA
SPEND TONIGHT

09:45.130 --> 09:46.893
HAVING CHRISTMAS EVE DINNER
WITH MY DEMENTED FAMILY

09:46.900 --> 09:48.959
IT'S GONNA BE
WEIRD ENOUGH WITHOUT ME
BEING HIGH ON CRACK.

09:48.960 --> 09:51.622
NO, IT'S JUST
CRYSTAL METH.

09:51.630 --> 09:54.758
IT JUST MAKES EVERYTHING
BURN A LITTLE BIT BRIGHTER.

09:56.030 --> 09:59.090
AND IT MAKES SEX
LIKE TOTALLY PRIMAL.

10:01.000 --> 10:02.820
HERE.

10:02.830 --> 10:04.457
IT'S ALRIGHT.

10:13.230 --> 10:15.698
OH, WELL,
IT'S TOO LATE NOW.

10:15.700 --> 10:16.894
( phone )

10:16.900 --> 10:18.527
IT'S MINE.

10:19.800 --> 10:21.256
HELLO ?

10:21.260 --> 10:22.693
DAVID, HI.

10:22.700 --> 10:24.622
HANG ON A SECOND.

10:29.400 --> 10:31.152
SO, IS NATE
THERE YET ?

10:31.160 --> 10:33.754
NO, HE'S STILL
AT THE AIRPORT.

10:33.760 --> 10:36.752
CLAIRE,
I'VE GOT BAD NEWS.

10:36.760 --> 10:38.352
WHAT ?

10:48.130 --> 10:50.325
UM...

10:50.330 --> 10:52.127
YEAH, SURE.

10:52.130 --> 10:54.052
OKAY,
I'M ON MY WAY.

11:02.160 --> 11:04.094
I HAVE TO GO.

11:04.100 --> 11:06.421
NO FUCKING WAY !

11:06.430 --> 11:08.990
WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT.

11:09.000 --> 11:11.889
YOU'RE COMING BACK,
RIGHT ?

11:11.900 --> 11:13.891
UH, I DON'T THINK SO.

11:13.900 --> 11:16.528
MY DAD JUST GOT
HIT BY A BUS

11:16.530 --> 11:20.125
AND IT BROKE HIS NECK
AND HE'S DEAD.

11:20.130 --> 11:23.122
I GOTTA GO PICK UP MY MOM
AND BRING HER TO THE MORGUE

11:23.130 --> 11:26.054
SO SHE CAN
IDENTIFY HIS BODY.

11:26.060 --> 11:27.857
( laughter )

11:28.730 --> 11:30.789
NO, I'M NOT KIDDING.

11:30.800 --> 11:32.620
THIS IS ACTUALLY
HAPPENING.

11:32.630 --> 11:34.598
AND NOW
I'M HIGH ON CRACK !

11:34.600 --> 11:35.692
CRYSTAL.

11:35.700 --> 11:37.156
WHATEVER !

11:37.160 --> 11:40.425
SO, I GUESS THIS WHOLE
HELLISH EXPERIENCE
I'M ABOUT TO GO THROUGH

11:40.430 --> 11:43.228
IS JUST GONNA BURN
A LITTLE BRIGHTER NOW, RIGHT ?

11:43.230 --> 11:44.822
GREAT,
THANK YOU !

11:44.830 --> 11:46.354
FUCK !

11:49.760 --> 11:51.193
( door slamming )

11:54.460 --> 11:56.052
YOU REALLY DIDN'T
HAVE TO DO THIS.

11:56.060 --> 11:57.755
I COULD'VE
JUST RENTED A CAR.

11:57.760 --> 11:59.125
IT'S OKAY.

11:59.130 --> 12:00.688
YOU'RE IN
NO SHAPE TO DRIVE.

12:00.700 --> 12:02.793
AND FRANKLY,
I'M IN NO HURRY TO GET HOME

12:02.800 --> 12:05.655
TO MY FAMILY'S ANNUAL
CHRISTMAS EVE MASSACRE.

12:05.660 --> 12:08.595
PARENTS WHO STAYED TOGETHER
FOR THE CHILDREN,

12:08.600 --> 12:09.658
BUT REALLY BECAUSE

12:09.660 --> 12:12.720
THEY GOT OFF ON TORMENTING
EACH OTHER SO MUCH.

12:12.730 --> 12:14.254
MANIC-DEPRESSIVE BROTHER

12:14.260 --> 12:18.594
WHO ALWAYS CHOOSES THE HOLIDAYS
TO GO OFF HIS MEDICATION.

12:18.600 --> 12:20.659
OH, AND AN ANCIENT
SPRINGER SPANIEL

12:20.660 --> 12:23.652
WHO'S COMPLETELY BLIND,
DEAF, AND INCONTINENT.

12:24.960 --> 12:26.894
WHAT ABOUT YOU ?

12:27.860 --> 12:30.693
UH, ACTUALLY,
WE'RE PRETTY NORMAL.

12:30.700 --> 12:32.850
MY MOM'S
A CONTROL FREAK.

12:32.860 --> 12:35.124
MY BROTHER, UM,

12:35.130 --> 12:37.951
WELL, HE'S A
CONTROL FREAK, TOO.

12:37.960 --> 12:40.793
AN D, MY SISTER...

12:40.800 --> 12:43.689
WELL, I LEFT HOME
RIGHT BEFORE SHE WAS BORN,

12:43.700 --> 12:45.918
SO I NEVER REALLY
KNEW HER THAT WELL,

12:45.930 --> 12:48.353
BUT SHE'S KIND OF WILD
LIKE I WAS.

12:48.360 --> 12:49.657
WAS ?

12:54.160 --> 12:57.129
MY DAD REALLY RODE MY ASS
WHEN I WAS A KID.

12:58.630 --> 13:02.088
I COULDN'T GO RAFTING
'CAUSE HE'D JUST BURIED
THIS GIRL WHO DROWNED.

13:02.100 --> 13:03.419
HE BURIES THIS
DIPSHIT LOSER

13:03.430 --> 13:05.250
WHO O.D.'d
AT A FLOCK OF SEAGULLS CONCERT,

13:05.260 --> 13:08.229
SUDDENLY I'M NOT ALLOWED
TO GO TO CONCERTS FOR A YEAR.

13:08.230 --> 13:09.857
YOUR DAD WORKED
IN A CEMETERY ?

13:09.860 --> 13:11.999
HOW COULD A MAN WHO'S
SO FUCKING SCARED OF EVERYTHING

13:12.000 --> 13:13.991
WHO NEVER
HAD AN A ACCIDENT

13:14.000 --> 13:16.252
OR EVEN A SPEEDING TICKET
IN HIS ENTIRE FUCKING LIFE,

13:16.260 --> 13:18.251
HOW COULD HE
HAVE A CAR WRECK ?

13:18.260 --> 13:20.148
ARE YOU MAD AT HIM,

13:20.160 --> 13:22.890
OR THE FACT THAT
WE'RE ALL GONNA DIE ?

13:22.900 --> 13:25.653
ARE YOU A SHRINK ?

13:25.660 --> 13:28.254
NO, GOD, NO !

13:28.260 --> 13:29.852
NO!

13:29.860 --> 13:31.623
BOTH MY PARENTS ARE.

13:35.600 --> 13:37.852
SO, WHAT ELSE DO YOU
WANT TO TALK ABOUT ?

13:37.860 --> 13:40.397
THE WEATHER ?

13:40.400 --> 13:45.019
OR THE FACT THAT WE BOTH JUST
FUCKED A PERFECT STRANGER ?

13:45.030 --> 13:48.852
AND THAT WE BOTH LIED WHEN
WE SAID WE NEVER DID THAT ?

13:52.630 --> 13:54.598
( chattering )

13:57.230 --> 13:58.857
( male )
WONDERFUL SERVICE.

13:58.860 --> 14:01.522
( female )
YES, IT WAS,
VERY NICE.

14:09.200 --> 14:10.929
AHH... !

14:11.660 --> 14:14.493
SHE LOOKED SO PEACEFUL,
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

14:14.500 --> 14:15.649
YOU'RE WELCOME.

14:15.660 --> 14:17.196
WONDERFUL JOB.

14:21.730 --> 14:23.823
DID YOU KNOW THAT
BEFORE YOU WERE BORN,

14:23.830 --> 14:25.957
FUNERAL HOMES RAN
THE AMBULANCE BUSINESS ?

14:25.960 --> 14:28.099
NO.

14:28.100 --> 14:30.455
HEARSES WERE
THE ONLY VEHICLES

14:30.460 --> 14:33.327
THAT COULD TRANSPORT
PEOPLE LYING DOWN.

14:33.330 --> 14:35.389
WOW.

14:35.400 --> 14:38.198
YOUR FATHER USED TO
JOKE ABOUT THAT.

14:38.200 --> 14:42.296
JUST DRIVE HIM AROUND
THE BLOCK A FEW MORE TIMES,

14:42.300 --> 14:44.655
AND WE WON'T NEED
TO STOP AT THE HOSPITAL.

14:44.660 --> 14:48.391
YOU'RE KIND OF
FREAKING ME OUT RIGHT NOW.

14:48.400 --> 14:50.994
CLAIRE...

14:51.000 --> 14:54.049
ARE YOU
HAVING SEX ?

14:54.060 --> 14:55.596
WHAT ?

14:55.600 --> 14:57.556
OR DOING DRUGS ?

14:57.560 --> 15:01.155
WHY ARE YOU ASKING ME
THIS RIGHT NOW ?

15:01.160 --> 15:03.924
YOUR FATHER IS DEAD.

15:03.930 --> 15:06.455
I CAN'T EVEN REMEMBER
THE LAST TIME

15:06.460 --> 15:09.190
YOU AND I TALKED
ABOUT ANYTHING IMPORTANT.

15:09.200 --> 15:12.294
I NEED TO KNOW
YOU'RE OKAY.

15:13.800 --> 15:15.825
OH, YEAH...

15:17.360 --> 15:20.397
BELIEVE ME,
I'M OKAY.

15:22.630 --> 15:24.655
YOU KNOW,
CONSIDERING.

15:31.230 --> 15:32.959
DO YOU WORK HERE ?

15:32.960 --> 15:34.427
UH, YES.

15:34.430 --> 15:36.990
I WANTED TO COMPLIMENT
YOU ON THE MUSIC.

15:37.000 --> 15:39.059
I'VE BEEN TO THREE OTHER
FUNERALS THIS YEAR.

15:39.060 --> 15:42.120
CANCER, STROKE,
PEDIATRIC LEUKEMIA,

15:42.130 --> 15:45.691
AND THE MUSIC IS ALWAYS
THAT SAME SAD ORGAN MUSIC.

15:45.700 --> 15:47.793
IT REMINDS ME OF THOSE
SOAP OPERAS MY MOM
USED TO WATCH

15:47.800 --> 15:49.688
BEFORE I STARTED
KINDERGARTEN.

15:49.700 --> 15:52.624
OH GOD, YOU'RE PROBABLY
TOO YOUNG TO REMEMBER THAT.

15:52.630 --> 15:55.451
ANYWAY, I SO PREFER
THIS LIGHT CLASSICAL,

15:55.460 --> 15:58.224
YOU KNOW,
CHAMBER ORCHESTRA STUFF.

15:58.230 --> 15:59.424
IT'S STILL SPIRITUAL,

15:59.430 --> 16:02.149
BUT DOESN'T SEEM
SO DATED OR DEPRESSING.

16:02.160 --> 16:03.457
I STUDIED
MUSIC APPRECIATION...

16:03.460 --> 16:05.098
( female voice )
YOU THINK I'M REALLY
BORING, DON'T YOU ?

16:05.100 --> 16:06.453
WELL, GET USED TO IT.

16:06.460 --> 16:08.018
BECAUSE NOW
THAT YOUR FATHER IS DEAD,

16:08.030 --> 16:10.123
YOU CAN FORGET ABOUT
EVER GOING LAW SCHOOL.

16:10.130 --> 16:12.724
IT'S JUST YOU, AND DEAD PEOPLE,
AND FREAKS LIKE ME

16:12.730 --> 16:14.357
FOR THE REST
OF YOUR LIFE !

16:14.360 --> 16:16.055
AAH...!

16:23.400 --> 16:24.958
MOM !

16:27.100 --> 16:28.988
MOM, I'M SO SORRY.

16:32.160 --> 16:33.821
WHO'S SHE ?

16:33.830 --> 16:35.991
AH...

16:36.000 --> 16:37.297
THIS IS, UM...

16:37.300 --> 16:38.597
BRENDA CHENOWETH.

16:38.600 --> 16:40.352
BRENDA...
CHENOWETH.

16:40.360 --> 16:42.225
UM, BRENDA,

16:42.230 --> 16:44.755
THIS IS MY MOM,
RUTH FISHER,

16:44.760 --> 16:48.025
AND MY SISTER,
CLAIRE.

16:48.030 --> 16:50.225
UM, NATE, CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND ?

16:50.230 --> 16:52.118
YEAH, JUST
GIVE ME A MINUTE.

16:52.130 --> 16:55.327
MOM, DID YOU
ALREADY DO THE--

16:55.330 --> 16:56.797
I CAN'T.

16:56.800 --> 16:58.825
I'VE SEEN TOO MANY
DEAD PEOPLE IN MY LIFE.

16:58.830 --> 16:59.956
THEY'RE WORK.

16:59.960 --> 17:02.053
I WON'T SEE
YOUR FATHER THAT WAY.

17:02.060 --> 17:03.755
I NEED YOU
TO DO IT.

17:03.760 --> 17:06.092
OH.

17:06.100 --> 17:08.625
NATE, I NEED TO TALK TO YOU
NOW, PLEASE, IT'S URGENT.

17:13.360 --> 17:16.227
SO, HOW DID YOU
AND MY SON MEET ?

17:16.230 --> 17:18.027
IN COOKING CLASS.

17:19.730 --> 17:22.028
I HAVE TO
TELL SOMEBODY.

17:22.030 --> 17:23.497
I AM TWEAKING.

17:23.500 --> 17:24.819
YEAH, WE'RE
ALL UPSET.

17:24.830 --> 17:26.889
NO, I'M HIGH
ON CRYSTAL.

17:26.900 --> 17:29.027
I SMOKED SOME WITH SOME FRIENDS
BEFORE DAVID CALLED ME.

17:29.030 --> 17:30.725
YOU DID WHAT ?

17:30.730 --> 17:32.391
DON'T WORRY,
IT'S THE FIRST TIME.

17:32.400 --> 17:33.697
BUT I THINK I'M HAVING
SOME KIND OF A MELTDOWN,

17:33.700 --> 17:36.919
AND I CAN'T TELL
IF IT'S DAD BEING DEAD
OR THE CRYSTAL.

17:36.930 --> 17:39.558
I'M REALLY SCARED.

17:39.560 --> 17:42.927
YOU CANNOT DO THIS
TO ME RIGHT NOW.

17:42.930 --> 17:45.990
DON'T BE SUCH A NARC,
WE SMOKED POT AT THANKSGIVING.

17:46.000 --> 17:48.696
LOOK, I HAVE TO GO IDENTIFY
OUR DEAD FATHER'S BODY.

17:48.700 --> 17:51.453
I'M SORRY YOU'RE HAVING
A BAD DRUG EXPERIENCE,

17:51.460 --> 17:53.291
BUT DEAL WITH IT.

18:14.800 --> 18:16.051
( unzippering )

18:19.900 --> 18:21.720
WELL ?

18:25.160 --> 18:26.821
( father's voice )
WELL, WELL.

18:26.830 --> 18:29.594
THE PRODIGAL RETURNS.

18:29.600 --> 18:31.420
THIS IS WHAT YOU'VE BEEN
RUNNING AWAY FROM

18:31.430 --> 18:33.421
YOUR WHOLE LIFE,
BUDDY BOY.

18:33.430 --> 18:34.920
SCARED THE CRAP
OUT OF YOU

18:34.930 --> 18:37.194
WHEN YOU WERE GROWING UP,
DIDN'T IT ?

18:37.200 --> 18:40.727
AND YOU THOUGHT YOU'D ESCAPE,
WELL, GUESS WHAT ?

18:40.730 --> 18:44.154
NOBODY ESCAPES.

18:49.530 --> 18:51.157
WELL ?

18:51.160 --> 18:53.128
YEAH,
THAT'S HIM.

18:57.300 --> 18:59.598
OKAY, LET'S
GET OUT OF HERE.

19:02.630 --> 19:04.825
HOW'D HE LOOK ?

19:04.830 --> 19:07.651
DEAD.

19:07.660 --> 19:11.118
WILL THERE NEED TO BE
A LOT OF RECONSTRUCTION ?

19:11.130 --> 19:14.850
DAVID'S NOT THAT SKILL
AT THE REALLY HARD STUFF.

19:14.860 --> 19:17.795
FEDERICO USUALLY DOES THAT,
HE'S QUITE GIFTED.

19:17.800 --> 19:22.157
YOU DON'T THINK WE'LL HAVE TO
HAVE A CLOSED CASKET, DO YOU ?

19:22.160 --> 19:25.049
I WOULD HATE TO
SEND THAT MESSAGE.

19:25.060 --> 19:26.220
WHAT MESSAGE ?

19:26.230 --> 19:28.721
THAT WE'RE NOT EQUIPPED
TO HANDLE A MAJOR RESTORATION,

19:28.730 --> 19:30.129
OR THAT WE'RE NOT
PROUD OF OUR WORK.

19:30.130 --> 19:31.995
MOM, CAN WE TALK
ABOUT THIS LATER ?

19:32.000 --> 19:33.991
WE SHOULD REALLY GET NATE HOME,
HE'S PROBABLY EXHAUSTED.

19:34.000 --> 19:35.695
LET'S GO.

19:45.930 --> 19:47.727
UM...

19:47.730 --> 19:49.698
THAN KS...

19:49.700 --> 19:50.928
FOR DRIVING
ME HERE.

19:50.930 --> 19:51.794
PLEASE.

19:51.800 --> 19:54.018
I'M JUST AVOIDING
MY OWN HELL.

19:54.030 --> 19:56.248
I'M A BIG COWARD.

19:58.230 --> 19:59.891
ME, TOO.

20:01.260 --> 20:03.649
I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN HANDLE THIS.

20:03.660 --> 20:07.699
WELL, YOU'RE ABOUT
TO FIND OUT.

20:09.600 --> 20:12.228
I WISH YOU
THE BEST, NATE.

20:12.230 --> 20:14.050
GOODBYE.

20:32.400 --> 20:34.493
CLAIRE...

20:34.500 --> 20:36.855
YOU'RE DRIVING
TOO FAST.

20:36.860 --> 20:39.499
THIS ISN'T FAST,
YOU WANNA SEE FAST ?

20:39.500 --> 20:41.855
( engine accelerates )

20:44.060 --> 20:45.925
PULL OVER !

20:55.700 --> 20:57.691
LISTEN, DO YOU
DO A LOT OF DRUGS ?

20:57.700 --> 20:58.997
WHAT ?

20:59.000 --> 21:00.092
NO.

21:00.100 --> 21:01.397
AND IT'S NONE OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

21:01.400 --> 21:02.549
YES, IT IS
MY BUSINESS.

21:02.560 --> 21:04.425
LOOK, YOU WERE DRIVING
LIKE A MANIAC BACK THERE,

21:04.430 --> 21:06.159
YOU COULD'VE
GOTTEN US ALL KILLED.

21:06.160 --> 21:07.320
WHAT THE HELL
IS THIS ?

21:07.330 --> 21:09.025
YOU'RE NOT
MY FATHER.

21:09.030 --> 21:11.157
YOU SPLIT AS SOON AS YOU COULD,
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW ME.

21:11.160 --> 21:13.856
SO, DON'T START THINKING YOU CAN
TELL ME WHAT TO DO, OKAY ?

21:22.560 --> 21:24.323
( door opening )

21:31.730 --> 21:35.291
SO, WHERE'S DAD,
DOWNSTAIRS ALREADY ?

21:35.300 --> 21:38.121
UM, HE'S STILL
IN THE MORGUE.

21:38.130 --> 21:40.223
YOU DIDN'T BRING HIM
BACK WITH YOU ?

21:40.230 --> 21:42.118
( mother)
OH, DEAR.

21:42.130 --> 21:45.497
THAT DIDN'T EVEN
CROSS MY MIND.

21:45.500 --> 21:48.856
WE SHOULD'VE TAKEN THE VAN
SO WE COULD BRING HIM HOME.

21:48.860 --> 21:50.896
I'M SORRY.

21:50.900 --> 21:53.528
THAT WAS VERY
STUPID OF ME.

21:59.560 --> 22:01.198
NICE GOING, DAVE.

22:01.200 --> 22:04.294
LIKE SHE DOESN'T HAVE ENOUGH
TO FEEL BAD ABOUT RIGHT NOW ?

22:04.300 --> 22:06.222
THINGS HAVE
TO BE DONE.

22:06.230 --> 22:08.357
FEDERICO'S DOWNSTAIRS,
READY TO START.

22:08.360 --> 22:09.657
EVERY SECOND WE WAIT

22:09.660 --> 22:11.890
WILL ONLY MAKE
DAD'S RESTORATION
MORE DIFFICULT.

22:11.900 --> 22:14.152
BUT YOU WOULDN'T KNOW
ABOUT THAT, WOULD YOU ?

22:14.160 --> 22:15.696
BAG BOY.

22:15.700 --> 22:18.294
"BAG BOY" ?

22:18.300 --> 22:21.827
I AM ASSISTANT MANAGER
OF ORGANIC PRODUCE

22:21.830 --> 22:24.253
AT THE HIGHEST VOLUME
FOOD CO-OP IN SEATTLE.

22:24.260 --> 22:26.023
JESUS, PULL YOUR DICKS OUT
AND MEASURE THEM,

22:26.030 --> 22:28.248
LET'S GET
THIS OVER WITH !

22:28.260 --> 22:30.399
WHAT WERE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO,

22:30.400 --> 22:32.595
JUST TH ROW DAD
IN THE BACK OF CLAIRE'S CAR ?

22:32.600 --> 22:34.352
IT IS A HEARSE !

22:34.360 --> 22:36.499
YEAH, HI,
IT'S DAVID FISHER.

22:36.500 --> 22:39.822
YEAH, SO I NEED TO COME
PICK UP THE BODY.

22:42.360 --> 22:44.396
( ghost )
Know you not
the family of the man

22:46.100 --> 22:48.591
from dawn to dark
these many years ?

22:48.600 --> 22:50.659
( Scrooge )
They appear
to be so happy...

22:50.660 --> 22:52.196
I MADE YOU
SOME DINNER.

22:52.200 --> 22:54.760
I'M SO
NOT HUNGRY.

22:54.760 --> 22:56.625
WE HAVE TO EAT,
CLAIRE.

22:56.630 --> 22:58.655
WE DIDN'T DIE.

23:04.630 --> 23:07.349
brother,
Tiny Tim.

23:16.930 --> 23:19.455
ON THREE,
ONE, TWO, THREE.

23:36.430 --> 23:38.250
REALLY SORRY, MAN.

23:38.260 --> 23:40.319
THAN KS.

23:51.660 --> 23:55.494
( male )
FOR A BODY THAT'S FIRM
YET FLEXIBLE,

23:55.500 --> 23:58.719
FOR SKIN THAT
BEGS TO BE TOUCHED.

23:58.730 --> 24:03.190
FOR THE VELVETY APPEARANCE
OF ACTUAL LIVING TISSUE,

24:03.200 --> 24:05.395
TOP MORTICIANS RELY

24:05.400 --> 24:08.597
ON LIVING SPLENDOR
EMBALMING FLUID.

24:08.600 --> 24:10.249
LIVING SPLENDOR...

25:03.060 --> 25:05.790
HEY, BUDDY BOY.

25:05.800 --> 25:08.519
COME ON IN,
IT'S OKAY.

25:11.460 --> 25:13.997
SAY HELLO
TO MR. BLOOMBERG.

25:14.000 --> 25:17.925
THERE ISN'T ANYTHING
TO BE AFRAID OF, NATE.

25:17.930 --> 25:20.228
MR. BLOOMBERG'S DEAD.

25:20.230 --> 25:22.551
AND I'M GETTING HIM READY
SO HIS FAMILY CAN SEE HIM

25:22.560 --> 25:24.289
FOR THE LAST TIME,
AND SAY GOODBYE TO HIM.

25:24.300 --> 25:26.097
IT'LL MAKE THEM
FEEL BETTER.

25:26.100 --> 25:29.319
THAT'S WHAT
DADDY DOES.

25:29.330 --> 25:32.128
WHAT DO YOU GOT ?

25:32.130 --> 25:34.098
BANG !

25:34.100 --> 25:36.660
OH !
YOU GOT ME.

25:39.030 --> 25:41.453
YOU CAN TOUCH HIM
IF YOU WEAR ONE OF THESE.

25:41.460 --> 25:44.395
BELIEVE ME,
HE WON'T MIND.

25:44.400 --> 25:46.356
HE WON'T CARE.

25:56.400 --> 25:58.197
NATE !

25:58.200 --> 26:00.657
WHAZZUP ?

26:05.030 --> 26:06.349
HEY, RICO.

26:06.360 --> 26:07.497
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

26:07.500 --> 26:09.229
OOH.

26:09.230 --> 26:11.357
REALLY SORRY
ABOUT YOUR DAD, MAN.

26:11.360 --> 26:14.591
BUT WHEN YOUR
TIME'S UP, IT'S UP, RIGHT ?

26:14.600 --> 26:16.659
( David )
HOW'S HE DOING ?

26:16.660 --> 26:20.391
SO FAR SO GOOD.

26:20.400 --> 26:21.424
I REALLY APPRECIATE

26:21.430 --> 26:23.227
YOU COMING IN
ON CHRISTMAS EVE, FEDERICO.

26:23.230 --> 26:25.528
IT'S THE LEAST
I COULD DO FOR MR. F,

26:25.530 --> 26:27.452
EVERYTHING
HE DID FOR ME.

26:27.460 --> 26:29.098
I WAS GONNA BE UP
ALL NIGHT ANYWAY,

26:29.100 --> 26:30.954
PUTTING TOGETHER
ALL THIS USELESS SHIT

26:30.960 --> 26:33.019
SANTA CLAUS IS BRINGING
MY KID, YOU KNOW ?

26:33.030 --> 26:35.021
WE DON'T USE THAT
KIND OF LANGUAGE IN HERE.

26:35.030 --> 26:36.998
SHOW SOME RESPECT.

26:42.630 --> 26:44.222
YOU NEED SOMETHING ?

26:44.230 --> 26:45.959
UH, NO.

26:45.960 --> 26:47.450
I JUST--

26:47.460 --> 26:49.155
( phone )

26:49.860 --> 26:50.952
DAVID FISHER.

26:50.960 --> 26:53.599
HEY, LISTEN,
I JUST WANT TO REMIND YOU,

26:53.600 --> 26:56.228
DON'T EAT TOO MUCH WITH
YOUR FAMILY TONIGHT, ALRIGHT ?

26:56.230 --> 26:58.892
'CAUSE I AM MAKING YOU
SOMETHING TOTALLY DECADENT

26:58.900 --> 27:00.458
AND FATTY
FOR DESSERT...

27:00.460 --> 27:03.520
HOLD JUST
A SECOND, PLEASE.

27:10.930 --> 27:12.397
HI.

27:12.400 --> 27:15.949
Keith, I'm sorry,
I can't make it.

27:18.200 --> 27:19.349
WHY NOT ?

27:19.360 --> 27:22.557
BECAUSE MY FATHER WAS JUST
KILLED IN A CAR ACCIDENT.

27:22.560 --> 27:24.755
OH, SHIT, DAVID,
I'M SO SORRY.

27:24.760 --> 27:26.625
Whathdo?

27:26.630 --> 27:29.793
NOTHING, THANKS,
BUT I HAVE TO STAY HERE.

27:29.800 --> 27:33.156
LISTEN, IF YOU NEED ANYTHING
DON'T HESITATE TO CALL ME.

27:33.160 --> 27:35.594
Sure.

27:35.600 --> 27:38.228
I MEAN IT, DAVID.

27:38.230 --> 27:41.051
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
GO THROUGH THIS ALONE.

27:41.060 --> 27:43.893
I GOTTA GO.

27:48.400 --> 27:50.197
OKAY, HERE IT GOES.

27:50.660 --> 27:52.753
THIS IS THE ONE
I'M MOST PROUD OF.

27:52.760 --> 27:55.058
THE HUSBAND,
OKAY ?

27:55.060 --> 27:57.699
HE GOT FIRED,
FLIPPED OUT,

27:57.700 --> 27:59.998
SHOT HIS WIFE
POINT BLANK IN THE HEAD,

28:00.000 --> 28:02.298
THEN TURNED IT AROUND
AND SHOT HIMSELF IN THE MOUTH.

28:02.300 --> 28:04.325
SOME SERIOUSLY
CLOSED CASKET SHIT, RIGHT ?

28:04.330 --> 28:06.025
NOW LOOK AT THIS.

28:06.030 --> 28:07.224
HUH ?

28:07.230 --> 28:11.018
LIKE THE BRIDE AND GROOM
ON TOP OF A CAKE.

28:13.460 --> 28:15.325
AND THEN
WE CREMATED 'EM.

28:15.330 --> 28:18.049
WHAT A FUCKIN' WASTE.

28:18.060 --> 28:20.255
OH...

28:20.260 --> 28:22.751
ACTUALLY...

28:22.760 --> 28:25.923
THIS RIGHT HERE IS,
THIS IS MY BEST WORK.

28:25.930 --> 28:30.458
WAIT A MINUTE,
THIS KID WAS BORN
JUST LIKE LAST MONTH.

28:30.460 --> 28:34.351
HE'LL BE FOUR FUCKING
YEARS OLD IN APRIL,
CAN YOU BELIEVE IT ?

28:34.360 --> 28:36.157
OH...

28:36.160 --> 28:38.890
VAN ESSA'S
PREGNANT AGAIN.

28:38.900 --> 28:42.119
YOU STUD !

28:42.130 --> 28:45.293
( Federico )
IT WASN'T PLANNED,
YOU KNOW WHAT ?

28:45.300 --> 28:47.427
NEITHER WAS
THIS ONE,

28:47.430 --> 28:49.955
AND HE'S THE BEST THING
THAT EVER HAPPENED TO ME.

28:51.100 --> 28:52.920
KEEP AN EYE ON
THOSE CHEMICALS, FEDERICO,

28:52.930 --> 28:55.148
WE DON'T
WANT HIM TO BURN.

29:09.460 --> 29:11.018
HEY.

29:13.600 --> 29:14.919
WHERE'S MOM ?

29:14.930 --> 29:16.693
SHE WENT TO BED.

29:16.700 --> 29:20.192
WAS SHE FEELING
ANY BETTER ?

29:20.200 --> 29:23.727
YEAH, NATE, SHE WAS ON TOP
OF THE GODDAMN WORLD.

29:30.130 --> 29:32.098
WHERE'S DAVID ?

29:32.100 --> 29:34.352
HE'S DOWNSTAIRS
WORKING.

29:34.360 --> 29:36.419
ON DAD ?

29:36.430 --> 29:39.797
YEAH, WELL,
HIM AND RICO.

29:43.460 --> 29:45.348
HE SAID NOT TO
WAIT UP FOR HIM,

29:45.360 --> 29:46.952
WE SHOULD JUST TRY
AND GET SOME SLEEP.

29:46.960 --> 29:49.520
YEAH, AS IF THAT WERE
A VIABLE OPTION.

30:11.960 --> 30:13.689
YOU WANT TO GO
TO THE GROCERY STORE ?

30:13.700 --> 30:16.498
YES, ANYTHING
TO GET OUT OF HERE.

30:35.400 --> 30:37.220
( phone )

30:38.660 --> 30:40.059
HELLO ?

30:40.060 --> 30:43.791
WELL, IT'S ABOUT TO START
RAINING FROGS HERE.

30:43.800 --> 30:45.756
HOW ARE THINGS
ON YOUR END ?

30:45.760 --> 30:47.227
GOD, I'M GLAD
YOU CALLED.

30:47.230 --> 30:48.549
Really, why ?

30:48.560 --> 30:51.597
I DON'T KNOW,
BECAUSE YOU, UH...

30:51.600 --> 30:53.898
YOU HAVE
A CALMING EFFECT ON ME.

30:53.900 --> 30:55.629
UH-HUH.

30:55.630 --> 30:59.122
ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH THE PSYCHOLOGICAL TERM
PROJECTION ?

30:59.130 --> 31:01.553
ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH THE PSYCHOLOGICAL TERM
"BLOW ME" ?

31:01.560 --> 31:03.858
Come on.

31:03.860 --> 31:06.192
You grew up with
all that psycho-babble.

31:06.200 --> 31:08.919
You rebelled against it
every chance you got, still do.

31:08.930 --> 31:10.488
And that includes

31:10.500 --> 31:12.923
HAVING SEX WITH STRANGERS
IN CLOSETS AT AIRPORTS.

31:12.930 --> 31:15.728
AND YOU THINK
YOU'RE NOT EASY TO READ ?

31:15.730 --> 31:17.823
Coasting by on
your looks and charm

31:17.830 --> 31:19.559
isn't working
like it used to,

31:19.560 --> 31:21.949
but, you have no idea
what else to do,

31:21.960 --> 31:23.598
because you've never
had to learn.

31:23.600 --> 31:25.227
ANY WOMAN
WITH HALF A BRAIN

31:25.230 --> 31:26.857
LOOKS AT A GUY LIKE YOU
AND THINKS,

31:26.860 --> 31:29.954
GOOD FOR A HOT FUCK,
BUT BELIEVE ME, THAT'S IT.

31:38.600 --> 31:41.455
NATE, CAN WE GO HOME ?
I REALLY GOTTA TAKE A SHOWER.

31:41.460 --> 31:43.098
OH, GOD,
JESUS CHRIST,

31:43.100 --> 31:46.149
AM I NOT ALLOWED TO HAVE EVEN
A SINGLE MOMENT TO MYSELF ?!

31:48.060 --> 31:49.493
ARGH !

31:52.360 --> 31:53.622
OKAY.

31:53.630 --> 31:55.495
IT'S OKAY.

31:55.500 --> 31:57.650
WHAT CAN I DO ?

31:57.660 --> 32:01.096
NOTHING,
NO ONE CAN DO ANYTHING.

32:07.460 --> 32:09.655
YOU'LL HAVE TO PAY
FOR THAT CANTALOUPE.

32:09.660 --> 32:11.525
YOU FUCK OFF !

32:20.500 --> 32:23.424
( female )
SHE LOOKED HER BEST
EVERY DAY OF HER LIFE.

32:23.430 --> 32:27.355
DON'T LET ONE HORRIBLY
DISFIGURING ACCIDENT
CHANGE THAT.

32:27.360 --> 32:30.557
USE NEW WOUND FILLER
COSMETIC MOLDING PUTTY.

32:30.560 --> 32:33.290
NOW FASTER SETTING
AND SELF SEALING

32:33.300 --> 32:36.895
TO HELP MAKE MASKING
UNSIGHTLY WOUNDS A BREEZE.

32:38.660 --> 32:40.753
SHE SAID
WHAT ABOUT TONIGHT

32:40.760 --> 32:44.594
SHE SAID, "TRUST ME, BABY,
IT'LL BE ALRIGHT"

32:44.600 --> 32:46.818
( loud music playing )

32:52.200 --> 32:53.519
( music shuts off)

32:53.530 --> 32:56.454
MA, REMEMBER THAT STUFFED DOG
I USED TO HAVE ?

32:56.460 --> 32:58.792
AND I DRAGGED IT AROUND
UNTIL ITS EARS FELL OFF,

32:58.800 --> 33:00.927
AND THEN YOU MADE NEW EARS
OUT OF A DISH TOWEL.

33:02.530 --> 33:04.851
AND I THREW IT
UP ON THE ROOF ?

33:04.860 --> 33:06.657
NO.

33:06.660 --> 33:09.390
AND THEN I WANTED IT BACK
AND I BEGGED DAD TO GO GET IT,

33:09.400 --> 33:11.197
BUT HE SAID NO,
IF I REALLY WANTED IT

33:11.200 --> 33:13.395
I'D NEVER HAVE THROWN IT
UP THERE IN THE FIRST PLACE.

33:13.400 --> 33:15.152
YOUR FATHER DID SO MANY
WONDERFUL THINGS FOR YOU,

33:15.160 --> 33:17.196
AND THAT'S ALL YOU CAN
THINK OF RIGHT NOW ?

33:17.200 --> 33:20.021
WHAT, I JUST
REMEMBERED IT.

33:20.030 --> 33:22.157
HE WAS
A GOOD MAN !

33:27.300 --> 33:29.120
I'M GOING RUNNING.

33:31.100 --> 33:32.749
( door closing )

33:42.530 --> 33:45.090
OH, NO,
YOU'RE DOING ME ?

33:45.100 --> 33:47.352
YOU'RE THE WORST ONE
WE'VE GOT.

33:47.360 --> 33:48.896
THAN KS, DAD.

33:48.900 --> 33:50.253
WHERE'S FEDERICO ?

33:50.260 --> 33:52.421
IT'S CHRISTMAS MORNING,
HE'S WITH HIS WIFE AND KID.

33:52.430 --> 33:53.624
HE'LL BE IN LATER.

33:53.630 --> 33:55.291
OOH, COULDN'T
THIS WAIT ?

33:55.300 --> 33:56.927
I DON'T WANT YOU
RUINING MY FACE.

33:56.930 --> 33:58.420
IT'S A LITTLE LATE
FOR THAT.

33:58.430 --> 33:59.454
NOT FUNNY.

33:59.460 --> 34:01.155
I NEED TO STAY BUSY
RIGHT NOW.

34:01.160 --> 34:03.048
SO, GO REORGANIZE
SOME FILES

34:04.960 --> 34:06.552
THAT'S WHAT
YOU'RE GOOD AT.

34:06.560 --> 34:09.427
YOU NEVER REALLY HAD
ANY APTITUDE FOR THIS STUFF.

34:09.430 --> 34:11.125
I KNOW.

34:11.130 --> 34:13.724
AND WHAT DID
I DO WITH MY LIFE ?

34:13.730 --> 34:17.222
I WENT TO SCHOOL TO LEARN
EXACTLY HOW TO DO THIS STUFF.

34:17.230 --> 34:20.028
OTHER KIDS MY AGE
WERE GOING TO FRAT PARTIES,

34:20.030 --> 34:21.952
I WAS DRAINING CORPSES

34:21.960 --> 34:24.827
AND REFASHIONING
SEVERED EARS
OUT OF WAX.

34:24.830 --> 34:26.752
THANK GOD I DIDN'T
LOSE AN EAR.

34:26.760 --> 34:28.990
I CAN ONLY IMAGINE
WHAT YOU'D DO WITH THAT.

34:29.000 --> 34:31.491
AND I DID IT
ALL FOR YOU.

34:31.500 --> 34:35.425
I DID IT TO MAKE YOU HAPPY,
YOU UNGRATEFUL SONOFABITCH.

34:36.600 --> 34:38.727
UM, DAVE ?

34:41.160 --> 34:43.651
I JUST WANTED TO
LET YOU KNOW I WAS HERE.

35:25.700 --> 35:27.850
( horn honking )

36:05.630 --> 36:08.497
WE'LL DEAL YOU IN
NEXT HAND.

36:19.230 --> 36:22.358
( soft music playing )

36:38.360 --> 36:40.692
I'M ABOUT TO JUMP
OUT OF MY SKIN.

